(firstQuint)Ginger Capsules for the Acute Treatment of Migraine Attacks.

 Patients with the diagnosis of migraine according to the IHS criteria were enrolled in the study during a migraine attack.

 Patients received two 200 mg capsules of dry ginger extract (5% active ingredient) or two capsules of placebo (cellulose) in addition to an intravenous dose of ketoprofen (100 mg) to treat the migraine attack.

